"title": "5264: compensation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5264",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Compensation under the law of Moses</h2>\n<h3>For personal injuries</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:26-Exod21:27\">EXO 21:26–21:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:32\">EXO 21:32</a></p>\n<h3>For the loss of an animal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:33-Exod21:34\">EXO 21:33–21:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:35-Exod21:36\">EXO 21:35–21:36</a></p>\n<h3>For theft</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:1\">EXO 22:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:3-Exod22:4\">EXO 22:3–22:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:7-Exod22:9\">EXO 22:7–22:9</a></p>\n<h3>For damage to property</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:5-Exod22:6\">EXO 22:5–22:6</a></p>\n<h3>For breach of trust</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:10-Exod22:15\">EXO 22:10–22:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:1-Lev6:7\">LEV 6:1–6:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:5-Num5:7\">NUM 5:5–5:7</a> <em>Compensation was only paid when someone was at fault.  Similar laws apparently existed in patriarchal times:  see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:39\">Ge 31:39</a>.</em></p>\n<h2>Compensation later in the OT</h2>\n<h3>The law applied by David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:4-2Sam12:6\">2SA 12:4–12:6</a></p>\n<h3>Sevenfold compensation for theft</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:30-Prov6:31\">PRO 6:30–6:31</a> <em>presumably “sevenfold” here means “manifold”; he will pay in full</em></p>\n<h3>Adultery beyond compensation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:32-Prov6:35\">PRO 6:32–6:35</a></p>\n<h3>Compensation a mark of repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:15\">EZK 33:15</a></p>\n<h2>Compensation in the NT</h2>\n<h3>For losses inflicted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a></strong> <em>In his zeal, after being converted, Zacchaeus goes beyond the requirements of the law.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:18-Phlm1:19\">PHM 1:18–1:19</a></p>\n<h3>For losses sustained for the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:29\">MAT 19:29</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:29-Luke18:30\">LUK 18:29–18:30</a> <em>God is far more generous under grace than he required wrongdoers to be under law.</em></p>",
